<br>
Here's what I did:<br>
<br>
It's late in 1999, and I need a car badly. So I go to a &quot;buy here, Pay bere&quot; car lot, and They tell me that no matter WHAT, they can finance me. <br>
<br>
Sure, I agree, and I get a 1994 Ford Probe with 76,000 Miles on it. Not too bad, It's in great shape, no rust or dings. Looks almost TOO new. So I drive it off the lot, not worrying about what I paid for it. I just know that I have to pay $239 a month. Not too bad....<br>
<br>
<br>
4 months goes by, no problems, Runs great everything.....<br>
<br>
5th month, the Transmission light starts to blink, so I ignore it, cause the car is still running great.<br>
<br>
6th month, Transmission completely fails, taking other parts with it, Speed sensor among those. So I take it to a transmission shop and tell them to fix it, whatever it costs. $2,500 later I have a brand new transmission. THEN the rubber thingie that holds the strut in place breaks, and my strut pokes out out my hood. Hood:$400, Struts and mount $600.<br>
<br>
I JUST paid this car off this month (november, 2003). Total priceL 10,800 (car) + $2,500 Transmission, + $600 Struts and stuffs, = $13,900.<br>
<br>
For a 9 year old car.. (5 when I bought it).<br>
<br>
I got taken, and I won't let it happen again. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=211851" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.wideopenwest.com/~canders4826/images/Dretta1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=heugel>Heugel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:green;'>Tavern Patron</span></span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/12/03 6:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5534.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB Used Car (help...!)</span><hr size=1> If you still live in the detroit area, make sure you check around the local circulars... Trading Times, Auto-Trader, etc.  I bought my first car, a 1983 Monte Carlo, for $1,000 out of the Trading Times back in '95.  That car lasted nearly 5 years, until my own stupid mistakes cost me an engine.  <br>
<br>
Get a mechanically inclined friend to check out stuff for you.  Drive it, make sure you like it, and always, always haggle.  Don't focus on used car lots, because you'll almost always overpay.  Concentrate on private owners, especially ones who just bought a new car (hint - Ford just released a new offer for A, D, and Z plan employees, so there should be a plethora of used cars on the market after first of the year). <br>
<br>
Also another thing you might want to check - there are a few public car auctions in the area that might be worth looking in to.  Check the yellow pages and call around.  <br>
<br>
If you have any more questions, shoot me an e-mail at mdheugel@hotmail.com.  I've got a couple friends who may be able to help you out if you get in a pickle and don't know which way to go.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=geldune>Geldune</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_yellowspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 59<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/12/03 7:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5534.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB Used Car (help...!)</span><hr size=1> omeone mentioned used cars from rental agencies.<br>
Enterprise occassionally emails me with reminders of their current vehicles for sale.  Could always check them out with financing options.  There are a few Enterprise offices out around the suburbs here in Detroit (assuming you are around here still) that list their cars.  <br>
Something like Geo Metro might not be all 'that hip', but maybe with a small downpayment and a purchase over 3-5 yrs, you could be on the way down the road.  I see a couple noted for around 6500.  Don't forget to check out insurance rates on anything you buy also!  You need to factor in plates as well.<br>
<br>
<a href="http://www.enterprise.com/carsales/messageTile.do?mtId=44" target="_new">Enterprise's Used Cars</a><br>
<br>
I wish I could recommend a good mechanic  to have check out anything you are considering, but I'm seeking out one of those myself and have no recommendation for anyone in Metro Detroit as of yet and most of my friends have newer cars and just go to the dealers mostly.<br>
<br>
 *sighs* I've been nothing but ticked off with the Ford Dealers, I've dealt with in the last two years for work on my T-Bird, because I've gotten some pretty stupid remarks made to me which make no sense.  {Latest one, My "Air filter was in backwards".  a- It's still the same way it was when I had brought it in. I know because I replaced it a week prior and they didn't 'flip' it.  b- If it was in backwards, um, the latches on the casing for it wouldn't shut!  It only goes in ONE WAY anyhow!  *grumbles*  Thanks Park Motor Sales (Ford-Lincoln/Mercury Dealer), but no thanks.}<br>
<br>
Getting a reliable used car for 2k would be rather hard pressed, IMO.  Especially around here where folk drive their cars into the ground, the potholes kill our suspensions and the salt just eats away our cars.<br>
<br>
If your job situation is stable and you have the ability to secure financing, try the purchase option and eventually you can move up and onward from whatever you  get as this starting point. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=salladarahn>salladarahn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:pink;'>Tavern Floor Sweeper</span></span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/12/03 7:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5534.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB Used Car (help...!)</span><hr size=1> I'm really surprised that so many people recommend buying used rental cars.<br>
