<br>
BEWARE the used rental. I see what these cars look like before we clean them up to sell them. Engines get steam cleaned, car gets a full detail etc.<br>
 <br>
People really thrash on rentals. In a cars life, it is good to go easy on it for about 1000 miles so seals can seat properly etc. Rentals do not get this luxury. They get hammered on from mile 1. Often needing engine or transmission repair at or near 50k miles.<br>
<br>
Also, do not buy from a dealership, they really overprice cars, private parties are the way to go IMO. Ask the person who is selling to let you take the car to your technician, they should have no problem with that. If they do, they are probably hiding something.<br>
Hope my novel helps <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://e.domaindlx.com/Makas/Makas_Manyhe_15691.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zenlaispentarrah>Zenlais Pentarrah</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:yellow;'>Tavern Ale Swiller</span></span><br>  Posts: 92<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/12/03 9:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5534.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: WTB Used Car (help...!)</span><hr size=1> A good thing to check (like someone already said) are the local auctions.<br>
