ex-Archon of Bristlebane</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub40.ezboard.com/bthesaryrntavern.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nemedra@thesaryrntavern>Nemedra</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><span style='color:blue;'>Tavern Regular</span></span><br>  Posts: 228<br> <font color=#6FB8DD>(11/13/03 1:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub40.ezboard.com/fthesaryrntaverncommonsroom.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5534.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> having not only worked in car dealerships for the better part of the last 3 years, but i spent about a year in the inventory control department.  What that means is I was in charge of pricing based off of what our dealership payed for X automobile.  <br>
<br>
You can all agree dealerships are cheap bastards and NEVER EVER EVER pay one damned penny over what a car is worth.  And I'm not talking this kelly blue book NADA bull shit.  They give what the car is honest to god worth at ROCk bottom.  Then for a 6k to 7k car we'd AUTOmatically slab on 4k gravy for ourselves.  that's 10k - 11k for a 5 year old economy car.  If it was a 2 year old Lincoln Navigator?  Minumum 6.5k gravy.<br>
<br>
One thing I will say having worked in BIG dealerships for quite a while...  Though the salesmen may be sharks...  The service department will make sure that car runs like a raped ape no matter how old or cheap it may be.  So while getting an extended warrenty is still a good idea, VERY seldome is that puppy gonna crap out on you after a hand full of months.  And don't automatically go for the nice pretty shiny one that they're selling cheap.  If the body &amp; interior look sweet and the car is at bargain basement prices...  The engine/tran/power train are toast within the year.<br>
<br>
And when you go to the negotiation table...  Be sure not to be a total dick head about the price...  Be nice, give 'em 1k gravy (ask them to knock off 2.5 -3k if your looking ecomony cars), because this is their pay check and it's not unfair that a store should make a proffit of their product...  Walmart does it, the mall does it, there's no reason the car dealer shouldn't make SOME proffit.  Just don't let them take you for all your worth and you should be A-Ok.<br>
<br>
<br>
